  "doc_id": "32614",
  "text": "Twenty Wistar male rats with a mean weight of 360 g were randomly assigned to one of four treatment groups ( = 5): simulation of surgery (SHAM), ischemia-reperfusion (IR), RC-Pre (RC-3095 Pre-LIRI), and RC-Post (RC Post-LIRI). RC-3095 was administered as a single dose to the left jugular vein 15 min before the induction of ischemia (RC Pre-IR group) and immediately after clamp removal (RC Post-IR group). All animals were observed for 120 min after reperfusion. RC-3095 (0.3 mg/1 mL) was diluted in normal saline, following the protocol described in previous studies conducted by our research group [CITATION_1] .",
